  "response": "The shortest completed cricket Test match in terms of playing time is the match between Australia and South Africa held in February 1932 at Melbourne Cricket Ground. The match lasted for just 5 hours and 53 minutes, with Australia winning by an innings and 72 runs. In terms of the number of balls bowled, the shortest Test match is the one between Australia and South Africa at Cape Town in February 1936, which lasted for only 656 balls. \n\nPlease note that records can vary slightly based on criteria such as the number of overs bowled or the duration of the match.",
